summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Five Hundred ($500.) Dollars out of the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of Nellie Bock for personal injuries received by her on the 20th day of December, 1913, between the hours of 7:00 and 8:00 A. M., while walking on the west side of Ninth Avenue, between Madison and Spring Streets, in said city, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
